For chemical substructures of drugs, the fingerprints defined by PubChem were calculated using PyBioMedÂ [41]. The chemical substructure matrix is built using the binary fingerprints (881 bits in total). With the target information of drugs, two binary feature matrices are constructed. The target protein domain matrix is a binary matrix in which the elements are 1 if the targets of drugs have the corresponding protein domains or 0 otherwise. There are 1307 unique protein domain features. In the target gene ontology matrix, the elements are set to 1 if the targets of drugs are annotated with the gene ontology terms. There are 3336 unique gene ontology features. For drug induced gene expression changes from LINCS L1000 project, only the values of the 978 landmark genes were kept. If the absolute value of the moderated z-score for a gene signature is bigger than 2, the signature value is set to 1 or âÂ 1 depending on the original sign of the moderated z-score, otherwise the signature value is set to 0. After that, the elements of the gene expression matrix are evaluated as the averages of signature values of each gene for each drug. Through above data processing, four feature matrices XpâRnÃdp\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
