				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\begin{aligned} TPR= & {} \frac{TP}{TP+FN} \end{aligned}$$\end{document}24FPR=FPFP+TN\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\begin{aligned} FPR= & {} \frac{FP}{FP+TN} \end{aligned}$$\end{document}where TP is true positive, FN is false negative, FP is false positive, TN is true negative. The AUC score is the area under the ROC curve. Depending on which type of averaging was performed, three kinds of AUC scores were calculated. Sample-AUC considers the average AUC score for each drug, macro-AUC calculates AUC scores for each side effect label and finds the mean, micro-AUC takes all known drug-side effect pairs as a positive label.

